import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['job_count'] = data.groupby('job')['count'].transform('sum')
    data = data.sort_values('job_count', ascending=False)
    top_job = data.iloc[0]['job']
    top_job_count = data.iloc[0]['job_count']
    plt.bar(data['job'], data['job_count'])
    plt.axhline(y=top_job_count, color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend([f'Top Job: {top_job} ({top_job_count:,.2f})'])
    plt.title('What is the most common job held in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('year')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['count'])
    plt.title('How has the number of people holding jobs changed over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sex_count = data.groupby('sex').size()
    plt.pie(sex_count, labels=sex_count.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of job holders?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, alpha=0.5, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['perc'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['perc'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['perc'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of percentage of people holding jobs?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
